commitResults.messageBody:
Currently, there are no assertions in the code of
Rizzler, which may lead to assumptions in the code
that turn out to be wrong.

Adding assertions to the code eliminates such
assumptions and improves code quality.

As a step towards including assertions into the
code, let's introduce assertions into the
FileStorage class to assert save file creation.

commitResults.messageTitle: Merge pull request #1 from Green-Tea-123/branch-A-Assertions
commitResults.messageBody: Add assertion at the end of FileStorage creation

commitResults.messageTitle: Extract methods in AddCommand for readability
commitResults.messageBody:
The codebase has some methods that are considerably lengthy,
which inhibits readability and by extension code quality.

Extracting portions of those methods out into new methods
reduces the length of each method, increasing the readability
of the codebase.

Let's increase the readability of the codebase by extracting
the input checking of AddCommand during command execution into separate
methods to reduce the length of the execute() function.

commitResults.messageTitle: Merge pull request #2 from Green-Tea-123/branch-A-CodeQuality
commitResults.messageBody: Extract methods in AddCommand for readability
